---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="Writing, made human.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">01 / A text linter for the age of generated prose</div>
    <h1>Make machine-written text sound human.</h1>
    <p class="lede">lawlint finds the clichés, legalese, and rhythmic tells that make AI-generated writing feel synthetic — then points toward something clearer.</p>
    <div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/playground">Try the playground</a><a class="button secondary" href="/download">Download lawlint</a><a class="button secondary" href="/docs/getting-started">Read the docs</a></div>
  </section>
  <section class="demo rule">
    <div class="section-label">02 / In practice</div>
    <div class="demo-grid">
      <div><h2>A second pair of eyes.</h2><p>Designed for legal teams, editors, and anyone who wants direct, credible prose without sanding away its character.</p></div>
      <div class="paper-demo">
        <div class="sample bad"><span class="mark">−</span><span>It is important to note that we <u>delve</u> into the <u>landscape of</u> obligations.</span></div>
        <div class="diagnostic">no-ai-cliches · replace with a direct verb</div>
        <div class="sample good"><span class="mark">+</span><span>We <strong>examine</strong> the parties’ obligations.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="install rule">
    <div><div class="section-label">03 / Start small</div><h2>Native tools, no account.</h2></div>
    <div><pre>curl -fsSL https://lawlint.com/install.sh | sh</pre><p>Install the native CLI in one line and keep linting in your terminal, scripts, and editors.</p><a href="/download">See CLI downloads →</a> <a href="/docs/sdk">Explore the SDK →</a></div>
  </section>
</Layout>
<style>
  .hero { padding: 8rem 0 9rem; max-width: 58rem; }
  .lede { max-width: 35rem; font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2vw, 1.5rem); color: var(--muted); margin: 2rem 0; }
  .actions { display: flex; gap: 0.8rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .rule { margin: 2rem 0 0; }
  .section-label { color: var(--muted); font: 0.72rem "IBM Plex Mono", monospace; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .demo { padding-bottom: 4rem; }
  .demo-grid, .install { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 5rem; }
  .paper-demo { border: 1px solid var(--line); background: #f8f4ed; padding: 1.4rem; }
  .sample { display: flex; gap: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.55; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .sample u { text-decoration-color: var(--oxblood); text-decoration-thickness: 2px; text-underline-offset: 0.14em; }
  .mark { color: var(--oxblood); font: 1rem "IBM Plex Mono", monospace; }
  .diagnostic { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 0.7rem; color: var(--oxblood); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); font: 0.7rem "IBM Plex Mono", monospace; }
  .good strong { font-weight: 600; }
  .install { padding-bottom: 5rem; }
  .install pre { margin: 0; }
  @media (max-width: 700px) { .hero { padding: 5rem 0; } .demo-grid, .install { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; } }
</style>
